"system is not trying to make use of the disk before removing it. On Linux "
"instances this typically involves unmounting any file systems mounted from "
"the volume. The OpenStack volume service cannot tell if it is safe to remove"
" volumes from an instance so it does what it is told. If a user tells the "
"volume service to detach a volume from an instance while it is being written"
" to you can expect some level of file system corruption as well as faults "
"from whatever process within the instance was using the device."
